# UI aesthetic (this project)

## Design tokens (PipeSay)

Use the existing palette in `dictation.py` — do not invent random hex values:

- Background `#09090b`, panel `#141416`, card `#1c1c1f`, border `#2e2e33`
- Text `#f4f4f5`, muted `#71717a`, accent `#6366f1`, record `#ef4444`
- Font: Segoe UI; hierarchy = 22 title / 17 CTA / 14 body / 11 meta

## Layout principles

- One primary action (record button) per screen; status line directly beneath.
- Generous padding (16–20px shell); rounded panels via `highlightthickness=1` frames.
- Clear sections: hero (record + meter) → live preview → finalized results.
- Live region shows partial suffix ` …` only; finalized text never flickers or duplicates.

## When improving UI

1. **Function first** — ship behavior, then polish; never swap the whole toolkit for looks alone.
2. **Minimal diff** — touch `_build_ui` and colors, not STT/session logic.
3. **Name the style** — e.g. "minimal dark, zinc + indigo accent, calm density" (not "make it pretty").
4. **Avoid** HTML-default gray boxes, cramped controls, mixing live + finalized in one scrolling blob.

## Web stack (only if project moves off Tkinter)

React + Tailwind + shadcn/ui; add `.mdc` rules per stack. Not applicable to current `dictation.py`.
